      "text": "docs/next/api-reference/sdk-node.mdx        ~324\nerror        TelemetryOptions is described as\n\"Telemetry labels reported by the worker\n(language, framework, project)\" with fields\namplitude_api_key suggesting it is anonymous-\nusage (iii-telemetry) telemetry, but it is\ndocumented on the Node SDK page without\ndisambiguation, potentially conflating the two\ntelemetry surfaces; the general.md rule requires\nbare \"telemetry\" always be disambiguated. —\nAdd a clarifying note indicating whether this\ntype relates to iii-telemetry (anonymous usage)\nor OpenTelemetry, and avoid using bare\n\"telemetry\" in the description.\nsdk-python.mdx        ~40        error        The\ninitialization example names the SDK handle iii\ninstead of worker, violating the SDK initialization\nvariable convention that requires worker =\nregister_worker(...). — Rename the variable from\niii to worker so the example reads worker =\nregister_worker('ws://localhost:49134',\nInitOptions(worker_name='my-worker')).\nsdk-python.mdx        ~154        error        The\ntelemetry field in InitOptions is described with\nbare \"Internal telemetry metadata\" without\ndisambiguating whether this is iii-telemetry\n(anonymous usage) or OpenTelemetry; the rules\nrequire always disambiguating \"telemetry\". —\nClarify in the description that TelemetryOptions\nis iii-telemetry (anonymous usage metadata), not\nOpenTelemetry configuration.\nsdk-python.mdx        ~192        error\nTelemetryOptions is documented inline on the\nSDK reference page without noting it belongs to\niii-telemetry (anonymous usage), risking\nconflation with the OpenTelemetry otel field\ndocumented just above it in InitOptions. — Add a\ndisambiguating note to the TelemetryOptions\ndescription making clear this is anonymous-\nusage telemetry, distinct from the\nOpenTelemetry surface.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~46        error        The\ninitialization variable is named iii instead of\nworker as required by the SDK initialization\nvariable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii\n= register_worker(...) to let worker =\nregister_worker(...) and update all subsequent\nuses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~118        error        The\ninitialization variable is named iii instead of\nworker as required by the SDK initialization\nvariable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii\n= register_worker(...) to let worker =\nregister_worker(...) and update all subsequent\nuses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~241        error        The\nshutdown description says \"Telemetry is flushed\ninside the connection thread\" using bare\n\"telemetry\" in a context that refers to\nOpenTelemetry (shutdown_otel()), violating the\nrule in general.md that bare \"telemetry\" must\nnot refer to OpenTelemetry surfaces. — Replace\n\"Telemetry is flushed\" with \"OTel telemetry is\nflushed\" or \"OpenTelemetry is flushed\".\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~259        error        The\nshutdown_async description uses bare\n\"telemetry\" (telemetry::shutdown_otel() context)\nto refer to the OpenTelemetry surface, violating\ngeneral.md's disambiguation rule. — Replace\n\"telemetry::shutdown_otel()\" reference prose\nwith explicit \"OTel telemetry\" or\n\"OpenTelemetry\" wording.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~324        error\nTelemetryOptions is described as \"Telemetry\nmetadata provided by the SDK to the engine\"\nusing bare \"telemetry,\" but this type contains\namplitude_api_key indicating it belongs to the\nanonymous-usage (iii-telemetry) surface, not\nOpenTelemetry — the description conflates the\ntwo and violates general.md's disambiguation\nrule. — Clarify whether this is anonymous-usage\ntelemetry or OTel and use the appropriate\nqualified term (\"anonymous usage telemetry\" or\n\"OpenTelemetry\").",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "docs/next/api-reference/sdk-node.mdx        ~324        error        TelemetryOptions is described as \"Telemetry labels reported by the worker (language, framework, project)\" with fields amplitude_api_key suggesting it is anonymous-usage (iii-telemetry) telemetry, but it is documented on the Node SDK page without disambiguation, potentially conflating the two telemetry surfaces; the general.md rule requires bare \"telemetry\" always be disambiguated. — Add a clarifying note indicating whether this type relates to iii-telemetry (anonymous usage) or OpenTelemetry, and avoid using bare \"telemetry\" in the description.\nsdk-python.mdx        ~40        error        The initialization example names the SDK handle iii instead of worker, violating the SDK initialization variable convention that requires worker = register_worker(...). — Rename the variable from iii to worker so the example reads worker = register_worker('ws://localhost:49134', InitOptions(worker_name='my-worker')).\nsdk-python.mdx        ~154        error        The telemetry field in InitOptions is described with bare \"Internal telemetry metadata\" without disambiguating whether this is iii-telemetry (anonymous usage) or OpenTelemetry; the rules require always disambiguating \"telemetry\". — Clarify in the description that TelemetryOptions is iii-telemetry (anonymous usage metadata), not OpenTelemetry configuration.\nsdk-python.mdx        ~192        error        TelemetryOptions is documented inline on the SDK reference page without noting it belongs to iii-telemetry (anonymous usage), risking conflation with the OpenTelemetry otel field documented just above it in InitOptions. — Add a disambiguating note to the TelemetryOptions description making clear this is anonymous-usage telemetry, distinct from the OpenTelemetry surface.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~46        error        The initialization variable is named iii instead of worker as required by the SDK initialization variable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii = register_worker(...) to let worker = register_worker(...) and update all subsequent uses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~118        error        The initialization variable is named iii instead of worker as required by the SDK initialization variable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii = register_worker(...) to let worker = register_worker(...) and update all subsequent uses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~241        error        The shutdown description says \"Telemetry is flushed inside the connection thread\" using bare \"telemetry\" in a context that refers to OpenTelemetry (shutdown_otel()), violating the rule in general.md that bare \"telemetry\" must not refer to OpenTelemetry surfaces. — Replace \"Telemetry is flushed\" with \"OTel telemetry is flushed\" or \"OpenTelemetry is flushed\".\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~259        error        The shutdown_async description uses bare \"telemetry\" (telemetry::shutdown_otel() context) to refer to the OpenTelemetry surface, violating general.md's disambiguation rule. — Replace \"telemetry::shutdown_otel()\" reference prose with explicit \"OTel telemetry\" or \"OpenTelemetry\" wording.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~324        error        TelemetryOptions is described as \"Telemetry metadata provided by the SDK to the engine\" using bare \"telemetry,\" but this type contains amplitude_api_key indicating it belongs to the anonymous-usage (iii-telemetry) surface, not OpenTelemetry — the description conflates the two and violates general.md's disambiguation rule. — Clarify whether this is anonymous-usage telemetry or OTel and use the appropriate qualified term (\"anonymous usage telemetry\" or \"OpenTelemetry\").",
