ization\nvariable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii\n= register_worker(...) to let worker =\nregister_worker(...) and update all subsequent\nuses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~118        error        The\ninitialization variable is named iii instead of\nworker as required by the SDK initialization\nvariable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii\n= register_worker(...) to let worker =\nregister_worker(...) and update all subsequent\nuses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~241        error        The\nshutdown description says \"Telemetry is flushed\ninside the connection thread\" using bare\n\"telemetry\" in a context that refers to\nOpenTelemetry (shutdown_otel()), violating the\nrule in general.md that bare \"telemetry\" must\nnot refer to OpenTelemetry surfaces. — Replace\n\"Telemetry is flushed\" with \"OTel telemetry is\nflushed\" or \"OpenTelemetry is flushed\".\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~259        error        The\nshutdown_async description uses bare\n\"telemetry\" (telemetry::shutdown_otel() context)\nto refer to the OpenTelemetry surface, violating\ngeneral.md's disambiguation rule. — Replace\n\"telemetry::shutdown_otel()\" reference prose\nwith explicit \"OTel telemetry\" or\n\"OpenTelemetry\" wording.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~324        error\nTelemetryOptions is described as \"Telemetry\nmetadata provided by the SDK to the engine\"\nusing bare \"telemetry,\" but this type contains\namplitude_api_key indicating it belongs to the\nanonymous-usage (iii-telemetry) surface, not\nOpenTelemetry — the description conflates the\ntwo and violates general.md's disambiguation\nrule. — Clarify whether this is anonymous-usage\ntelemetry or OTel and use the appropriate\nqualified term (\"anonymous usage telemetry\" or\n\"OpenTelemetry\").",
