nvention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii = register_worker(...) to let worker = register_worker(...) and update all subsequent uses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~118        error        The initialization variable is named iii instead of worker as required by the SDK initialization variable convention in sdks.md. — Rename let iii = register_worker(...) to let worker = register_worker(...) and update all subsequent uses in the example.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~241        error        The shutdown description says \"Telemetry is flushed inside the connection thread\" using bare \"telemetry\" in a context that refers to OpenTelemetry (shutdown_otel()), violating the rule in general.md that bare \"telemetry\" must not refer to OpenTelemetry surfaces. — Replace \"Telemetry is flushed\" with \"OTel telemetry is flushed\" or \"OpenTelemetry is flushed\".\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~259        error        The shutdown_async description uses bare \"telemetry\" (telemetry::shutdown_otel() context) to refer to the OpenTelemetry surface, violating general.md's disambiguation rule. — Replace \"telemetry::shutdown_otel()\" reference prose with explicit \"OTel telemetry\" or \"OpenTelemetry\" wording.\nsdk-rust.mdx        ~324        error        TelemetryOptions is described as \"Telemetry metadata provided by the SDK to the engine\" using bare \"telemetry,\" but this type contains amplitude_api_key indicating it belongs to the anonymous-usage (iii-telemetry) surface, not OpenTelemetry — the description conflates the two and violates general.md's disambiguation rule. — Clarify whether this is anonymous-usage telemetry or OTel and use the appropriate qualified term (\"anonymous usage telemetry\" or \"OpenTelemetry\").",
