      "updated": 1782243561747,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Fix / Change: (See comments also, this is not all of the changes)\n\n--help output is not correctly formatted\n\nCommands in --help should be grouped based on relation AND alphabetized within each group\n\niii worker add/reinstall/update should ALWAYS re-run setup and install scripts. Currently it doesn't which leads\nto confusion when a user modifies their app dependencies, reinstalls (or add --force) and app dependencies do not update.\n\nSeveral commands need to accept multiple arguments (array): add, update, remove, reinstall, clear, stop, start, restart, status,\nexec, logs\n\niii worker sandbox needs to be removed in favor of iii trigger once iii trigger supports async/streaming upload/download\n\nSome subcommands commands accept --address and --port, some don't. With the further decentralization of iii's workers it will\nbe\nnecessary to specify iii worker --address localhost --port 49134 subcommand and have that apply wherever necessary.\n\niii must be able to know everything about a worker such that a user can run iii worker status, stop, log, etc. from one host to\naffect a worker on another host\n\nThe following subcommands can be reduced to iii trigger versions: list, status, logs, console.\niii worker commands should remain for convenience but users should be made aware that these are aliases\n\niii worker status must be adjusted to tail stdout so it's always showing the latest log message, currently it doesn't so workers\nwith long startup times (or those building rust binaries) look stalled when they're not",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "biiQZbHjPr8uo36d6Eh8e",
      "originalText": "Fix / Change: (See comments also, this is not all of the changes)\n\n--help output is not correctly formatted\n\nCommands in --help should be grouped based on relation AND alphabetized within each group\n\niii worker add/reinstall/update should ALWAYS re-run setup and install scripts. Currently it doesn't which leads\nto confusion when a user modifies their app dependencies, reinstalls (or add --force) and app dependencies do not update.\n\nSeveral commands need to accept multiple arguments (array): add, update, remove, reinstall, clear, stop, start, restart, status, exec, logs\n\niii worker sandbox needs to be removed in favor of iii trigger once iii trigger supports async/streaming upload/download\n\nSome subcommands commands accept --address and --port, some don't. With the further decentralization of iii's workers it will be\nnecessary to specify iii worker --address localhost --port 49134 subcommand and have that apply wherever necessary.\n\niii must be able to know everything about a worker such that a user can run iii worker status, stop, log, etc. from one host to affect a worker on another host\n\nThe following subcommands can be reduced to iii trigger versions: list, status, logs, console.\niii worker commands should remain for convenience but users should be made aware that these are aliases\n\niii worker status must be adjusted to tail stdout so it's always showing the latest log message, currently it doesn't so workers\nwith long startup times (or those building rust binaries) look stalled when they're not",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
