    {
      "id": "x1vU6LBdX-uIGCMkJW_Uq",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1651.7746363272863,
      "y": 5168.8621097753785,
      "width": 1324.5474853515625,
      "height": 765,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": "X6Ym6GEADxhdcPC6WKQn7",
      "index": "b3nr",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 102673942,
      "version": 1157,
      "versionNonce": 1214063754,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782243494448,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is a running worker?\n\nRunning worker = A process connected to iii\n\niii does not manage the workers connected to it\n\niii can provide all of the information necessary to start/stop/restart/otherwise\nmanage a worker from the localhost of that worker\n\niii cli can request all the information necessary to manager workers from iii engine\n\niii cli can manage all of the workers at its localhost\ndocker can manage all of the docker workers at its localhost\nsystemd/launchd/bash scripts/bare commands in a tmux session can\nmanage all of the non-containerized worker processes however users want to\n\na iii system can be any combination of the above",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "tEDkt4sEsHN3p_ecqxhoL",
      "originalText": "What is a running worker?\n\nRunning worker = A process connected to iii\n\niii does not manage the workers connected to it\n\niii can provide all of the information necessary to start/stop/restart/otherwise\nmanage a worker from the localhost of that worker\n\niii cli can request all the information necessary to manager workers from iii engine\n\niii cli can manage all of the workers at its localhost\ndocker can manage all of the docker workers at its localhost\nsystemd/launchd/bash scripts/bare commands in a tmux session can\nmanage all of the non-containerized worker processes however users want to\n\na iii system can be any combination of the above",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "iRbh5LyhEg8uy0y7ELmnt",
