      "name": "System design and extension"
    },
    {
      "id": "_BVZQneAAS4FVEWkNiGB3",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": -1806.742134202228,
      "y": -1342.879681667032,
      "width": 1626.885936465925,
      "height": 2310.457124667032,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3p",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 245630614,
      "version": 917,
      "versionNonce": 1944729366,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "tJgxpviB2Zr_Y1WTnD5W9"
        }
      ],
      "updated": 1782244959066,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "tJgxpviB2Zr_Y1WTnD5W9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1801.742134202228,
      "y": -1337.879681667032,
      "width": 1616.36328125,
      "height": 2025,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "dashed",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3q",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1221772246,
      "version": 2937,
      "versionNonce": 1261563594,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782245317431,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "This approach:\n\nUser onboarding\n\n1. Enhances user onboarding and understanding of iii with multiple touchpoints\n2. Enables user onboarding email flows (currently only iii.dev signups)\n3. Enhances user tracking in Posthog with email collection\n4. Reduces user error in tutorials\n5. Makes tutorials programmatically testable\n\nResult: CICD verifiable tutorials, A targeted attempt to increase activation\n\nWorker runtime definitions & Configuration\n\n1. Eliminates the need for iii-exec\n2. Enables multiple copies of the same worker to co-exist with their own isolated runtime and\nconfiguration details\n3. Enables worker-manager and sandbox to both run outside of the iii engine's host\n4. Allows for easy transition from config.yaml -> configuration-worker\n5. Leverages existing Sergio/Anderson work to decouple individual worker configs\n6. Decouples process management from the iii engine core\n7. Provides a simple path from quickstart -> development -> deployment\n8. Keeps all tutorials as a single `iii --compose` command for simplicitly while exposing users to the\nconcept of `iii worker compose`\n\n\nResult: iii-exec, config.yaml no longer need to exist\n\nCLI:\n\n1. Enables any commonly needed functionality to be available as a simple command in place of a\nTUI\n2. Simple and easy to update\n3. Easy for existing tooling to pipe and parse\n4. Easy for Agents to use\n5. Eliminates several unnecessary iii worker commands, adds one command (compose), and\nrenames one for clarity (verify -> validate; optional)\n\nResult: No need for TUI, trivial to expand feature set as needed\n\nConsole:\n\n1. Anderson migrating iii console to console worker\n\nResult: Removes iii console command",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": "_BVZQneAAS4FVEWkNiGB3",
      "originalText": "This approach:\n\nUser onboarding\n\n1. Enhances user onboarding and understanding of iii with multiple touchpoints\n2. Enables user onboarding email flows (currently only iii.dev signups)\n3. Enhances user tracking in Posthog with email collection\n4. Reduces user error in tutorials\n5. Makes tutorials programmatically testable\n\nResult: CICD verifiable tutorials, A targeted attempt to increase activation\n\nWorker runtime definitions & Configuration\n\n1. Eliminates the need for iii-exec\n2. Enables multiple copies of the same worker to co-exist with their own isolated runtime and configuration details\n3. Enables worker-manager and sandbox to both run outside of the iii engine's host\n4. Allows for easy transition from config.yaml -> configuration-worker\n5. Leverages existing Sergio/Anderson work to decouple individual worker configs\n6. Decouples process management from the iii engine core\n7. Provides a simple path from quickstart -> development -> deployment\n8. Keeps all tutorials as a single `iii --compose` command for simplicitly while exposing users to the concept of `iii worker compose`\n\n\nResult: iii-exec, config.yaml no longer need to exist\n\nCLI:\n\n1. Enables any commonly needed functionality to be available as a simple command in place of a TUI\n2. Simple and easy to update\n3. Easy for existing tooling to pipe and parse\n4. Easy for Agents to use\n5. Eliminates several unnecessary iii worker commands, adds one command (compose), and renames one for clarity (verify -> validate; optional)\n\nResult: No need for TUI, trivial to expand feature set as needed\n\nConsole:\n\n1. Anderson migrating iii console to console worker\n\nResult: Removes iii console command",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
